transcript: Patient: Fever and cough for 3 days. Doctor: Any shortness of breath? Patient: Mild sometimes.

soap_notes.subjective: Patient reported fever and cough for the last three days, with mild shortness of breath that occurs occasionally.
soap_notes.objective: No physical findings noted on examination.
soap_notes.assessment: Upper respiratory infection or pneumonia. Considering influenza in differential diagnosis due to symptoms duration and severity.
soap_notes.plan: Refer to infectious disease specialist if condition does not improve after 48 hours.

treatment_plan: Supportive care including hydration, rest, and symptomatic treatment for fever (if present).
